Functional Dependencies

1)actor(username->password,role_name)
2)activity_category(id->activity_name)
3)re_rule(re_rule_code->activity_category_code,nums_points,version,status)
4)rr_rule(rr_rule_code->reward,num_points,version,status)
5)brand(id->name,address,join_date,user_name)
6)loyalty_program(id->program_name,brand_id,tier_type,state)
7)re_rule_for_lp(lp_code,re_rule_code->lp_code,re_rule_code)
8)rr_rule_for_lp(lp_code,rr_rule_code->lp_code,rr_rule_code)
9)activities_for_loyalty_program(activity_lp_map_id->loyalty_program_code,activity_category_code)
10)customer(id->name,phone,address,user_name)
11)tier(id-> name, points, multiplier, lp_program_id)
12)customer_redeem_activity(id -> customer_id,activity_date,redeem_lp_map_id,points)
13)customer_activity(id -> customer_id,activity_date,activity_lp_map_id, customer_redeem_activity_id,points)
14)reward_category(id -> reward_name)
15)wallet(id -> points,customer_id,loyalty_program_code)
16)customer_lp_enroll(customer_id,loyalty_program_code -> customer_id,loyalty_program_code)
17)rewards_for_loyalty_program(reward_lp_map_id->loyalty_program_code,reward_category_code,reward_count,reward_value)

All above relation have primary keys and they determine the entire relation. So all relations are in BCNF.

